Force tuxedo_is_compatible() to return true.

Rationale: SCHENKER VISION M23 is hardware-identical to TUXEDO InfinityBook
Pro 16 Gen8 — both are Tongfang PH6PG01/PH6PG71 barebones on NB02 mainboard.
Only the DMI vendor string differs ("SchenkerTechnologiesGmbH" vs "TUXEDO").
The upstream compatibility check is marketing policy, not technical gating
("Going forward we only run the drivers on in house tested devices").

Without this patch, tuxedo_keyboard and NB02/NB04/NB05 modules refuse to
load on Intel 13th Gen+ CPUs (CPU fallback skips DMI only for pre-12th-Gen).
Result: no TCC Battery Care, no fan curves, no keyboard backlight control.

---
 src/tuxedo_compatibility_check/tuxedo_compatibility_check.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/tuxedo_compatibility_check/tuxedo_compatibility_check.c b/src/tuxedo_compatibility_check/tuxedo_compatibility_check.c
--- a/src/tuxedo_compatibility_check/tuxedo_compatibility_check.c
+++ b/src/tuxedo_compatibility_check/tuxedo_compatibility_check.c
@@ -220,6 +220,11 @@ static const struct dmi_system_id tuxedo_dmi_string_match[] = {
 };

 bool tuxedo_is_compatible(void) {
+	// PATCH (moonflyers-bluefin-dx): Force compatibility for baugleiche
+	// Tongfang-Rebrands (z.B. Schenker Vision M23 = TUXEDO InfinityBook
+	// Pro 16 Gen8). Hardware ist identisch, nur der DMI-Vendor unterscheidet.
+	return true;
+
 	if (dmi_check_system(tuxedo_dmi_string_match)
 	    || (x86_match_cpu(skip_tuxedo_dmi_string_check_match)
 	    && !x86_match_cpu(force_tuxedo_dmi_string_check_match))) {
